raw_data.title: Database Designer
raw_data.description: The Database Designer Develops relational databases for various systems as well as delivers instructional technologies for online courses and collaborative tools. They conduct Web design, instructional systems design, and multimedia design activities, and produce Web-based content. They develop and disseminate computer-based instructional products and courses. They will perform management system operation, including data and network maintenance and management activities. Liaise across the intelligence customer enterprise and with Mission Partners to facilitate cross-organizational training and file sharing.  Develop detailed and thorough knowledge of database schema, database operations and database communication layers; Design large scale changes to database technology as needed. They will develop a thorough and detailed understanding of the relational database platforms, with a focus on performance analysis, query optimization operations, appropriate SQL syntax and database internals. They will perform independent database performance analysis with a focus on SQL query efficiency and schema design; apply tools and utilities to identify integrity or performance issues. They will create white papers from research to support database initiatives; create internal documentation for educating and training employees and work with other development teams to review database queries and advise use of best practices using common data layer. Their goal will be to maintain Database Development Lifecycle Review database schema changes and generated queries as needed; assist and mentor developers with schema and query reviews. The candidate will work with teams to enforce database standards; aid in design and research of new database standards as needed.

raw_data.title: Supply Management Analyst I
raw_data.description: The Supply Management Analyst I provides scheduled supportability analyses, including a summary report of systems analyzed. Provides supportability analysis for groups of National Stock Numbers (NSN) associated with specific customer driven requirements. Provides “deep look” or “deep dive” supportability analysis of Industrial Product Support Vender (IPV) bench stock items associated with specific weapon systems at the respective customer location. Work in conjunction with the Defense Logistics Agency (DLA) Contracting Officer and Contracting Officer Representative to assign and schedule work load that surfaces from the customers to address both on-going and ‘ad hoc’ analysis requests. Establish realistic workload and timelines for project completion. Identify anticipated stock outages and work in conjunction with assigned Supply Management Analysts, and Procurement Technicians to minimize the number of stock outages and maximize support to the customer. Identify priority level of effort for potential stock outages. Collaborate with DLA or commercial suppliers to accelerate material purchases to close anticipated support gaps. Attend scheduled Government meetings to brief the supportability analysis findings.
